♻️ EcoSort AI
AI-Powered Waste Classification & Sustainable Disposal Assistant
📖 Overview

Waste management is one of the biggest environmental challenges facing the world today. Improper disposal of recyclable, hazardous, and organic waste contributes to pollution, increases landfill accumulation, contaminates natural resources, and reduces the efficiency of recycling systems.

EcoSort AI is an Artificial Intelligence-powered web application designed to simplify waste segregation. By uploading an image of a waste item, users receive an instant prediction of the waste category along with environmentally responsible disposal instructions, information about its environmental impact, and practical recycling suggestions.

Built using Streamlit and TensorFlow, EcoSort AI combines an intuitive user interface with deep learning to make waste classification accessible to everyone, regardless of their technical background.

The primary objective of this project is to promote sustainable waste management practices and encourage responsible disposal through the use of Artificial Intelligence.

🌍 Problem Statement

Many people struggle to identify the correct way to dispose of different types of waste. Items such as batteries, plastics, glass, paper, and textiles often end up in incorrect waste bins due to a lack of awareness. This leads to:

Increased environmental pollution
Reduced recycling efficiency
Contamination of recyclable materials
Growth of landfill waste
Harmful effects on ecosystems and human health

EcoSort AI addresses this challenge by automatically identifying waste categories from images and educating users on proper disposal methods.

