⚙️ How EcoSort AI Works

The application follows a simple workflow:

Step 1 – Upload Image

The user uploads one or more images of waste items through the Streamlit web interface.

Step 2 – Image Preprocessing

The uploaded image is resized and normalized to match the input requirements of the trained deep learning model.

Step 3 – AI Prediction

The TensorFlow model analyzes the image and predicts the most likely waste category.

Step 4 – Confidence Verification

The application evaluates the prediction confidence. If the uploaded image is unclear or unrelated to waste, the user receives a warning requesting a better image.

Step 5 – Result Display

For valid predictions, EcoSort AI displays:

Detected waste category
Proper disposal method
Environmental impact
Recycling and handling suggestions

This entire process is completed within a few seconds.

🧠 Artificial Intelligence Model

EcoSort AI uses a TensorFlow-based deep learning model trained to recognize ten categories of waste.

The model processes uploaded images and predicts the most suitable waste category. To improve prediction quality, the application performs image preprocessing before inference and validates prediction confidence before displaying results.

